{
  "id": "jsonbored_gittensory_425",
  "repo_name": "jsonbored/gittensory",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/jsonbored/gittensory",
  "base_commit": "e299ccd8d8403378aa50a020e13f7c75d8ab590f",
  "pr_number": 425,
  "issue_number": 424,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Public PR panel \"Duplicate risk\" count uses `Math.max` of two cluster sources instead of their union, so the posted comment's count disagrees with the related-work items it lists",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n`buildPublicPrIntelligenceComment` (`src/signals/engine.ts`) builds the public PR panel comment posted on pull requests. It derives the scoped-overlap count for the \"Duplicate risk\" table row from the **maximum** of two cluster-source lengths:\n\n```ts\n// src/signals/engine.ts:3436-3438\nconst prCollisionClusters = pullRequestSpecificCollisionClusters(args.collisions, args.pr);\nconst linkedDuplicatePrs = linkedIssueDuplicatePullRequests(args.pr, prCollisionClusters);\nconst scopedOverlapCount = Math.max(prCollisionClusters.length, args.preflight.collisions.length);   // <- max, not union\n```\n\n`scopedOverlapCount` feeds the \"Duplicate risk\" row's status/action text:\n\n```ts\n// src/signals/engine.ts:3506\n[\"Duplicate risk\", duplicateRiskStatus(linkedDuplicatePrs, scopedOverlapCount), duplicateRiskAction(linkedDuplicatePrs, scopedOverlapCount, gateBlocking)],\n\n// src/signals/engine.ts:3590-3593\nfunction duplicateRiskStatus(linkedDuplicatePrs: number[], scopedOverlapCount: number): string {\n  if (linkedDuplicatePrs.length > 0) return `Clear same-issue overlap: ${formatPrRefs(linkedDuplicatePrs)}`;\n  if (scopedOverlapCount > 0) return `${displayScopedCount(scopedOverlapCount)} scoped related-work signal${scopedOverlapCount === 1 ? \"\" : \"s\"}`;\n  return \"No PR-specific duplicate found\";\n}\n```\n\nBut the **details** section of the *same comment* lists the deduplicated **union** of those two cluster sources:\n\n```ts\n// src/signals/engine.ts:3512 (used to render the \"Review context\" details block)\nconst overlapDetails = relatedWorkDetails(args.pr, prCollisionClusters, args.preflight.collisions);\n\n// src/signals/engine.ts:3626-3638\nfunction relatedWorkDetails(pr: PullRequestRecord, prCollisionClusters: CollisionCluster[], preflightCollisions: CollisionCluster[]): string[] {\n  const clusters = [...new Map([...prCollisionClusters, ...preflightCollisions].map((cluster) => [cluster.id, cluster])).values()];   // <- union, deduped by id\n  // ...lists up to 4, then: `Additional scoped related-work signals hidden: ${clusters.length - summaries.length}.`\n}\n```\n\nSo one part of the comment counts with `max(|A|, |B|)` and the other part lists `|A \u222a B|`. These are not equal whenever the two sources are not subset/equal.\n\n## Why the two sources differ (so max \u2260 union)\n\nBoth come from the same `buildCollisionReport(...).clusters` (shared `id` scheme), but they are filtered by **different criteria**:\n\n- `prCollisionClusters` = clusters whose items include **this PR** (`pullRequestSpecificCollisionClusters`, `engine.ts:3574`).\n- `args.preflight.collisions` = clusters that **term-overlap the planned contribution** (the PR's title/body/files), filtered in `buildPreflightResult` via `termOverlap(plannedTerms, collisionTerms(item))`.\n\nA cluster can be in one set but not the other:\n- A cluster containing this PR may not term-overlap the planned terms (e.g. a linked-issue cluster whose title text doesn't overlap).\n- A cluster term-overlapping the planned contribution may involve **other** PRs/issues and not contain this PR at all.\n\nSo the sets are genuinely different subsets, and their union can exceed `max(|A|, |B|)`.\n\n## Observable failure (concrete example)\n\nFor a PR where `prCollisionClusters = {A, B}` (2) and `args.preflight.collisions = {B, C, D}` (3):\n\n- `scopedOverlapCount = Math.max(2, 3) = 3`.\n- The \"Duplicate risk\" row renders: **\"3 scoped related-work signals\"**.\n- `relatedWorkDetails` dedupes the union `{A, B, C, D}` = **4** and lists all four (or 4 shown / hidden count derived from 4).\n\nSo the posted PR comment's summary table claims **3** scoped related-work signals while the details block directly below it enumerates **4**. A maintainer reading the panel sees the headline count undercount the related work the same comment then lists \u2014 undermining trust in the panel and potentially under-stating duplicate/overlap risk on a PR. The mismatch grows with the number of clusters unique to each source.\n\nNote `displayScopedCount` caps the display at `9+`, but that does not fix the discrepancy below that cap (3 vs 4, etc.), and the same understated value also feeds `duplicateRiskAction` (\"Advisory review only.\" vs \"No action needed.\").\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Build a public PR panel (`buildPublicPrIntelligenceComment`) for a PR where the set of collision clusters containing the PR and the set of preflight (planned-term-overlap) clusters are not identical (e.g. the PR sits in one cluster while the planned terms overlap two other clusters).\n2. Compare the \"Duplicate risk\" row count to the number of items listed in the \"Review context\" related-work details.\n3. Observe the row shows `max(|prClusters|, |preflightClusters|)` while the details list `|prClusters \u222a preflightClusters|`.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nThe \"Duplicate risk\" count and the related-work details reflect the **same** set of clusters \u2014 the deduplicated union of `prCollisionClusters` and `args.preflight.collisions` \u2014 so the headline count always equals (or correctly summarizes) the items listed below it.\n\n## Actual behavior\n\n`scopedOverlapCount` is `Math.max(prCollisionClusters.length, args.preflight.collisions.length)`, which understates the deduplicated union that `relatedWorkDetails` renders, so the posted comment's count and its own details disagree.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nCompute the deduplicated union once and use it for both the count and the details:\n\n```ts\nconst scopedOverlapClusters = [...new Map([...prCollisionClusters, ...args.preflight.collisions].map((cluster) => [cluster.id, cluster])).values()];\nconst scopedOverlapCount = scopedOverlapClusters.length;\n// ...\nconst overlapDetails = relatedWorkDetails(args.pr, scopedOverlapClusters);   // pass the same deduped set (refactor relatedWorkDetails to take the union directly)\n```\n\nThis guarantees the \"Duplicate risk\" row count matches the related-work items listed in the details block. Add fail-on-revert coverage: a PR whose PR-specific clusters and preflight clusters are disjoint must render a \"Duplicate risk\" count equal to the number of distinct related-work clusters listed in the panel details (e.g. disjoint sets of sizes 2 and 3 \u2192 \"4 scoped related-work signals\", not \"3\").",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-06T00:06:28.000Z",
